defaultAgroecology
default has been defined as the application of ecological science to the study,
default 
defaultdesign and management of sustainable agroecosystems.
default&#xa0;default3.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAn
default evolution to agro ecological 
defaultwould provide many advantages, delivering food security and an increased resilience to climate ch
defaultange. Such strategies also offer greatly increased ecosystems services whilst providing a mechanism to sequestrate large amounts of both carbon and water back into the landscape
